- 'college-goers' refers to 'student' segment in the user data;
- 'interaction counts' pertain to the total number of interactions including views, likes, shares, and comments;
- 'most active ones' are determined by descending order of total interactions.

sql:
SELECT user_id, AVG(duration) AS average_interaction_duration
FROM user_interactions
GROUP BY user_id;

SELECT u.user_name, ui.interaction_type, ui.datetime
FROM users u
JOIN user_interactions ui ON u.user_id = ui.user_id;

